00:05:46.149 --> 00:05:49.750
Turns out, I gave Lily the same advice that brothers gave me.

00:05:51.189 --> 00:06:00.329
It was my turn to apply it. I had to be honest with myself. My limitation was my own high

00:06:00.329 --> 00:06:09.689
expectations. I've been doing it so long that there was no quick fix. It didn't mean giving up on my

00:06:09.689 --> 00:06:22.860
goals though. I just tried to focus more on what I could do in the present, like having more empathy

00:06:22.860 --> 00:06:36.120
for people who feel like I do and showing them how much Jehovah values them. We could tell about

00:06:36.199 --> 00:06:42.839
the student how we overcame a challenge.

00:06:43.879 --> 00:06:52.329
True this, I can actually do a lot for Jehovah with the reasonable expectations.

00:06:57.000 --> 00:07:03.160
Our sister learned to manage her anxiety in part by managing her expectations,

00:07:03.959 --> 00:07:11.720
a crucial step to giving her best to Jehovah. That lesson is an excellent introduction to this

00:07:11.720 --> 00:07:21.980
month's theme, realistic expectations, the key to joyful and successful service. When you hear

00:07:21.980 --> 00:07:30.779
the word realistic, what comes to your mind? Realistic conveys the idea of something that is practical,

00:07:30.779 --> 00:07:39.420
rational, reasonable, and sensible. Having expectations that are realistic is essential to

00:07:39.420 --> 00:07:49.420
joy and success in Jehovah's service. In contrast, unrealistic expectations cause discouragement

00:07:49.420 --> 00:07:59.420
as Proverbs 13-12 says, expectation postponed makes the heart sick, but a desire realized is a

00:07:59.420 --> 00:08:07.420
tree of life. Appropriately, we often use this verse when referring to expectations that are not

00:08:07.420 --> 00:08:16.620
achieved as quickly as we would like. However, expectations that are too high can also make our

00:08:16.620 --> 00:08:27.259
heart sick. Notice this quote from the August 8, 1983 issue of a wake. Disappointment is often

00:08:27.259 --> 00:08:35.500
not so much a matter of expectation postponed, as expectations too high. Now at times it is good to

00:08:35.500 --> 00:08:43.820
have high goals to aim for the stars, but always expecting to come out on top is a surefire way

00:08:43.820 --> 00:08:53.179
to beckon disappointment. To avoid disappointment, our expectation should be reasonable and sensible.

00:08:54.860 --> 00:09:01.259
In our discussion, we're going to answer the following three questions about our expectations.

00:09:01.740 --> 00:09:08.779
Number one, why must we be realistic about what we expect from ourselves?

00:09:10.220 --> 00:09:16.059
Number two, why must we be realistic and what we expect from our brothers and sisters?

00:09:17.500 --> 00:09:25.820
And number three, why is it realistic to expect that Jehovah will reward us for our faithful sacred

00:09:25.820 --> 00:09:34.919
service? Our first question is, why must we be realistic about what we expect from ourselves?

00:09:36.360 --> 00:09:43.159
Of course, we love Jehovah with our whole heart, mind and soul, and we want to do everything for

00:09:43.159 --> 00:09:51.720
his glory. However, the reality is that no matter how much we love Jehovah and want to obey him,

00:09:52.279 --> 00:10:00.679
we are sinful descendants of Adam. As a result, we occasionally transgress and thought word

00:10:00.679 --> 00:10:10.039
indeed. Ecclesiastes 7.20 states, for there is no righteous man on earth who always does good

00:10:10.039 --> 00:10:19.799
and never sins. And James 3.2 reads, for we all stumble many times. If anyone does not stumble in

00:10:19.799 --> 00:10:27.720
word, he is a perfect man. Perhaps you can relate to the feelings of the Apostle Paul at Romans chapter

00:10:27.720 --> 00:10:38.600
7, verses 18-20. For I know that in me, that is in my flesh, there dwells nothing good,

00:10:39.240 --> 00:10:44.759
where I have the desire to do what is fine, but not the ability to carry it out.

00:10:45.720 --> 00:10:53.000
For I do not do the good that I wish, but the bad that I do not wish is what I practice.

00:10:54.039 --> 00:10:59.879
If then, I do what I do not wish, I am no longer the one carrying it out,

00:11:00.519 --> 00:11:08.360
but it is the sin dwelling in me. Paul struggled with his sinful flesh, made him feel miserable.

00:11:09.320 --> 00:11:18.039
At times, we too might feel dejected, disappointed, and frustrated over our shortcomings.

00:11:19.320 --> 00:11:27.559
We may begin to feel like a failure. What enabled Paul to continue serving Jehovah with joy and zeal?

00:11:29.240 --> 00:11:35.240
He honestly acknowledged his sinful condition and had complete confidence in the ransom sacrifice

00:11:35.240 --> 00:11:41.639
of Jesus Christ. Paul went on to say at Romans 7, 24 and 25,

00:11:43.240 --> 00:11:48.919
miserable man that I am. Who will rescue me from the body undergoing this death?

00:11:50.360 --> 00:11:58.840
Thanks to God through Jesus Christ, our Lord. Yes, through Jehovah's undeserved kindness and his

00:11:58.840 --> 00:12:05.240
loving provision of the ransom, we can confidently remain in Jehovah's love and render worship

00:12:05.240 --> 00:12:14.200
that is acceptable to him, even in our imperfect state. How powerful is the ransom in allowing us

00:12:14.200 --> 00:12:22.039
to have a clean conscience and retain Jehovah's approval? Acts chapter 3 verse 19 answers this

00:12:22.039 --> 00:12:29.639
question. Repet therefore, and turn around so as to get your sins blotted out,

00:12:30.440 --> 00:12:37.320
so that seasons of refreshing may come from Jehovah himself. The original language word translated

00:12:37.320 --> 00:12:44.919
blotted out means to cause to disappear by wiping, to remove so as to leave no trace.

00:12:45.399 --> 00:12:49.320
Jehovah completely wipes out our sin.

00:12:51.240 --> 00:12:58.120
Till a straight. Imagine a white riding surface representing our clean standing before Jehovah.

00:12:58.840 --> 00:13:06.360
Now, imagine that red dots are drawn on it representing our sins. We should not view the ransom as

00:13:06.360 --> 00:13:13.720
if Jehovah draws an X over each dot to cross them out. Those red dots would still be visible.

00:13:14.679 --> 00:13:22.039
Rather, we should imagine Jehovah based on the ransom completely erasing the red dots

00:13:22.039 --> 00:13:29.639
so that a clean white riding surface is restored. Jehovah further reassures us of the completeness

00:13:29.639 --> 00:13:35.879
of his forgiveness with the words recorded at Psalm 103 verses 12 through 14.

00:13:36.600 --> 00:13:45.080
Jehovah remembers that we are dust and does not expect perfection from us.

00:13:46.759 --> 00:13:53.559
As a merciful Father, he puts our sins as far off as the sunrise is from the sunset.

00:13:55.639 --> 00:14:03.480
Even if a servant of Jehovah commits a serious sin, if he is truly repentant with godly sadness,

00:14:04.440 --> 00:14:15.080
his sin can be blotted out completely forgiven. Therefore, it is essential for us to maintain a

00:14:15.080 --> 00:14:23.480
reasonable, sensible, realistic view of our imperfect state. We're going to make mistakes,

00:14:24.759 --> 00:14:31.000
but we must have full trust in the reality of Jehovah's forgiveness based on the ransom.

00:14:31.799 --> 00:14:39.159
Also, we can learn valuable lessons from our errors so that we'll be less likely to repeat them.

00:14:41.259 --> 00:14:48.539
We need patience, though, because some personality flaws and bad habits may not go away overnight.

00:14:49.740 --> 00:14:59.580
Some of them may even be a lifelong battle. At times, we may need counsel and discipline.

00:15:00.299 --> 00:15:04.299
What should we realistically expect when receiving discipline?

00:15:05.899 --> 00:15:13.019
Hebrews 12, 11 through 13, makes it clear that initially it will not be joyous.

00:15:14.220 --> 00:15:21.899
It is painful. However, when we humbly accept discipline and apply the counsel,

00:15:22.700 --> 00:15:28.139
we can be sure that we will gain inner peace and be a better servant of Jehovah.

00:15:29.580 --> 00:15:34.860
Therefore, do not give up, but keep making progress.

00:15:36.620 --> 00:15:40.539
Never allow the devil to convince you that you are a failure.

00:15:42.059 --> 00:15:47.820
As stated in the September 1, 2001 issue of the Watchtower on page 18,

00:15:49.929 --> 00:15:55.610
Satan would like nothing better than to rob you of your peace. He would surely like you to feel

00:15:55.610 --> 00:15:59.929
that your imperfection makes your service unacceptable to God.

00:16:01.049 --> 00:16:08.330
Never allow the devil to demoralize you. Our second question for consideration is,

00:16:09.529 --> 00:16:14.250
why must we be realistic and what we expect from our brothers and sisters?

00:16:16.250 --> 00:16:21.769
Just as it's essential to avoid having expectations that are too high for ourselves,

00:16:22.809 --> 00:16:26.889
we must also avoid expecting too much from our brothers and sisters.

00:16:27.450 --> 00:16:34.809
Such unreasonable expectations create stress, disappointment, and frustration.

00:16:36.330 --> 00:16:42.009
The awake of September 8, 1994 quoted a factory supervisor who said,

00:16:43.929 --> 00:16:49.450
you have to accept people as they are. If you expect more than they can give,

00:16:50.250 --> 00:16:55.049
you will elevate the stress level, making everyone unhappy.

00:16:57.960 --> 00:17:03.480
We should expect from our fellow workers what Jehovah and Jesus expect from them.

00:17:05.079 --> 00:17:11.559
Jesus' illustration of the talents recorded in Matthew chapter 25 conveys their thinking.

00:17:13.240 --> 00:17:20.759
The main point of this illustration is that the master Jesus expects each of his anointed brothers,

00:17:20.759 --> 00:17:25.640
the slaves, and by extension those who are of the other sheep,

00:17:26.519 --> 00:17:31.799
to do his or her best in the assigned work of preaching the good news.

00:17:33.640 --> 00:17:40.279
How did Jesus distribute the work? Matthew chapter 25 verse 15 provides the answer.

00:17:42.279 --> 00:17:49.480
He gave five talents to one, two to another, and one to still another,

00:17:50.200 --> 00:17:55.160
to each according to his own ability, and he went abroad.

00:17:56.200 --> 00:18:03.480
Jehovah and Jesus are pleased with, and will reward each of us when we do our best within

00:18:03.480 --> 00:18:09.720
our circumstances and ability. When the slave of two talents gained two more,

00:18:10.599 --> 00:18:16.440
the master did not say to him, why did you not gain five more like your fellow slave?

00:18:16.599 --> 00:18:25.640
He gave the two talent slave the same commendation as the one who was given the five and gained five more.

00:18:26.920 --> 00:18:36.039
Well done, good and faithful slave. You were faithful over a few things. I will appoint you over

00:18:36.039 --> 00:18:45.079
many things. Enter into the joy of your master. As a result, the two talent slave could be just

00:18:45.079 --> 00:18:53.720
as successful and joyful as the five talents lay. They both met their master's reasonable

00:18:53.720 --> 00:19:01.160
expectations, and their master was joyful too. What a fine lesson for all of us,

00:19:02.039 --> 00:19:09.880
including those serving as elders. In imitation of Jehovah and Jesus, we should never put pressure

00:19:09.880 --> 00:19:16.599
on our brothers to do more than they're capable of doing. Failure to take this reasonable and

00:19:16.599 --> 00:19:25.880
realistic approach can result in much frustration. Another way that we show we have reasonable

00:19:25.880 --> 00:19:33.400
expectations is to acknowledge that from time to time disagreements and hurt feelings will arise

00:19:33.400 --> 00:19:40.839
among our brothers. Have you ever heard someone say, I expect to be treated that way by the world,

00:19:40.839 --> 00:19:47.240
but not by my brother? Is it reasonable to expect that there will not be any difficulties

00:19:47.240 --> 00:19:54.759
among brothers? No. Does Jesus expect that at times his disciples will have difficulties

00:19:54.759 --> 00:20:04.839
among themselves? Yes. Why can we say this? Remember some of the expressions Jesus used throughout

00:20:04.839 --> 00:20:12.380
the sermon on the mount. Happy are the peacemakers since they will be called sons of God.

00:20:14.059 --> 00:20:19.660
If you're bringing your gift to the altar, and there you remember that your brother has something

00:20:19.660 --> 00:20:28.619
against you, leave your gift there in front of the altar and go away. First, make your peace with

00:20:28.700 --> 00:20:38.779
your brother and then come back and offer your gift. Forgive us our debts as we also have forgiven

00:20:38.779 --> 00:20:49.099
our debtors. Stop judging that you may not be judged. These verses show that Jesus knew his

00:20:49.099 --> 00:20:57.819
disciples would have challenges among themselves. That was a realistic expectation, but it's also

00:20:57.819 --> 00:21:03.900
reasonable to conclude that these problems can be successfully resolved if godly principles

00:21:03.900 --> 00:21:12.220
are applied. Then peace can be restored. Additionally, we should expect some tensions to arise

00:21:12.220 --> 00:21:20.140
among the brotherhood today. But by applying Bible principles, peace can be restored and maintained.

00:21:22.700 --> 00:21:29.500
We'll now consider our third question. Why is it realistic to expect that Jehovah will reward

00:21:29.740 --> 00:21:37.420
us for our faithful sacred service? At Hebrews 116, the Bible tells us that Jehovah is the

00:21:37.420 --> 00:21:47.019
rewarder of those earnestly seeking him. And at 1 Corinthians 1558, the Apostle Paul encourages us to

00:21:47.019 --> 00:21:57.420
have plenty to do in the work of the Lord knowing that your labor is not in vain. Paul was absolutely

00:21:57.420 --> 00:22:04.539
sure of his heavenly reward. Despite his sins prior to becoming a Christian and his battles with

00:22:04.539 --> 00:22:13.180
sinful inclinations, please note his confidence expressed at 2 Timothy chapter 4 verses 7 and 8.

00:22:14.859 --> 00:22:22.059
I have fought the fine fight. I have run the race to the finish. I have observed the faith.

00:22:22.859 --> 00:22:29.339
From this time on, there is reserve for me the crown of righteousness, which the Lord, the

00:22:29.339 --> 00:22:37.420
righteous judge, will give me as a reward in that day, yet not to me only, but also to all those

00:22:37.420 --> 00:22:44.539
who have loved his manifestation. We can have similar confidence and the reward Jehovah has promised.

00:22:45.500 --> 00:22:51.660
Whether our hope is heavenly or to enjoy everlasting life on a paradise earth,

00:22:53.259 --> 00:22:59.900
this is a realistic expectation because our reasonable and loving God has promised it,

00:23:00.619 --> 00:23:10.299
and he does not lie. Therefore, may we develop and maintain realistic expectations for ourselves

00:23:10.940 --> 00:23:19.099
and for our fellow workers. May we never lose sight of the reality that Jehovah will reward those

00:23:19.099 --> 00:23:27.579
earnestly seeking Him. If we have realistic expectations, we can find joy and success in our

00:23:27.579 --> 00:23:41.019
service to Jehovah now, as well as have the prospect of doing so forever, young ones. No doubt you

00:23:41.019 --> 00:23:48.619
have many expectations for the life that lays ahead of you. Be assured that Jehovah wants the best

00:23:48.619 --> 00:23:54.940
for you and will give you Holy Spirit and the direction you need to make good choices.

00:23:57.019 --> 00:24:04.220
But what can you do if you make a decision that in the end disappoints you or those who love you?

