us all to go to our house. I started thinking about what might happen if I said yes to that girl's

00:26:26.579 --> 00:26:35.460
invitation. I knew that there'd be drinking, drugs, and maybe even something a moral might happen.

00:26:36.259 --> 00:26:43.539
So after having not prayed for a really long time, I closed my eyes and said, Jehovah, please help me.

00:26:45.299 --> 00:26:52.819
I'm just so alone, I don't have anyone. I felt completely abandoned by everyone.

00:26:53.779 --> 00:26:59.859
So right then and there, I said I prayed to Jehovah asking him that if he would help me to say no,

00:26:59.859 --> 00:27:05.059
from that day forward, I would stop associating with those friends and serve him whole-sold.

00:27:05.059 --> 00:27:10.339
Many times, I asked Jehovah to forgive me. I said, Jehovah, you're the only one I have.

00:27:11.859 --> 00:27:18.660
Please help me. And that's exactly what happened. After saying that prayer, I felt determined to leave.

00:27:19.619 --> 00:27:25.380
I started thinking about everything that I'd done and how I was putting not only my own life at risk,

00:27:25.380 --> 00:27:30.099
but also my relationship with Jehovah. I thought I'm going to talk to the elders.

00:27:30.819 --> 00:27:36.339
Since I'm a very shy person, the thought of confessing my mistakes was really difficult.

00:27:36.339 --> 00:27:42.099
I talked to them and I told them everything that happened. It was like a weight had been lifted off me.

00:27:42.099 --> 00:27:49.059
I saw that I really wasn't alone after all. I still remember a scripture that they read to me

00:27:49.059 --> 00:27:55.779
at Psalm 86.5, which showed me that Jehovah's forgiveness has no limits if I'm truly repentant.

00:27:55.779 --> 00:28:00.579
So I knew that Jehovah would forgive me, but the elders also told me that I'd have to tell my parents,

00:28:01.940 --> 00:28:08.420
which was very difficult. But I thought, well, I need to speak up and I just opened up

00:28:09.140 --> 00:28:18.009
and told them about what happened. I decided that I was going to talk with an elder,

00:28:18.009 --> 00:28:24.329
and he read a scripture with me from Philippians 4.7, which says that the peace of God that surpasses

00:28:24.329 --> 00:28:32.089
all understanding will guard our hearts. So I was able to pray again, knowing that if I really

00:28:32.089 --> 00:28:38.410
changed, I could feel that peace that comes from Jehovah. I started studying the Bible for you.

00:28:39.210 --> 00:28:44.569
I stopped associating with those friends and started being more involved in spiritual things.

00:28:45.450 --> 00:28:50.329
I had the privilege of getting baptized and becoming a regular pioneer, and today I'm serving in

00:28:50.329 --> 00:28:55.690
Bethel. I had the privilege of being invited to help with construction projects, but my greatest

00:28:55.690 --> 00:29:01.609
privilege is the strong friendship that I have with Jehovah and also having true friends.

00:29:02.170 --> 00:29:09.049
I've seen that Jehovah has always been by my side, and even when I didn't want to be with him,

00:29:09.049 --> 00:29:35.539
